        <summary>Is Cavalry Portfolio Services a legitimate company?</summary>
        <p>Yes, they are a legitimate debt collection firm. They are not a scam, but they are a very aggressive collections agency. If you receive a letter or a call from them, it means they believe you owe a debt that they have legally purchased.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can Cavalry Portfolio Services sue me?</summary>
        <p>Yes, as a debt buyer, Cavalry Portfolio Services has the legal right to file a lawsuit against you to recover the debt, provided the debt is still within your state's statute of limitations. Ignoring them can lead to a default judgment against you.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I stop Cavalry Portfolio Services from calling me?</summary>
        <p>Under the Fair Debt Collection Practices Act (FDCPA), you have the right to request that they stop contacting you. You must send them a written 'Cease and Desist' letter. Once received, they are legally required to stop calling, though they can still pursue legal action.</p>
      </details>
